{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 14:31:52.162456", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope\n- Validate fabric health in a 3-tier EBGP Clos topology.\n- Detect anomalies, localize potential faults, and identify root causes based on current state (control/data planes).\n\nExecutive Summary\n- Data plane: Host-to-host connectivity is healthy with zero loss and low, stable RTTs.\n- Control plane: All EBGP sessions are Established across the fabric. All expected prefixes are originated and propagated. Forwarding entries are consistent with the topology.\n- No service-impacting anomalies detected. One benign asymmetry observed (explained below), and one design observation (lack of ECMP on super-spine) that is not a fault.\n\nData Plane Validation\n- Reachability tests:\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 0% loss, avg RTT ≈ 2.385 ms\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: 0% loss, avg RTT ≈ 2.438 ms\n- Assessment: East–west host connectivity across leaves is normal. No packet loss, jitter very low.\n\nControl Plane (BGP) Status\n- Super-spine (AS 65000)\n  - Neighbors: spines 65100 (172.16.0.1) and 65101 (172.16.0.3) — both Established.\n  - PfxRcd: 2 from each spine (the two /24 leaf networks).\n  - RIB: Installs both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.1 (spine 65100). Single best-path per prefix chosen (no ECMP).\n- Spine 65100 (spine_router_0_0)\n  - Neighbors: super-spine 65000, leaves 65200 (172.16.0.5) and 65201 (172.16.0.7) — all Established.\n  - PfxRcd: 1 from each leaf, 0 from super-spine (see “Benign Asymmetry” below).\n  - RIB: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.5; 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.7; expected.\n- Spine 65101 (spine_router_0_1)\n  - Neighbors: super-spine 65000, leaves 65200 (172.16.0.9) and 65201 (172.16.0.11) — all Established.\n  - PfxRcd: 2 from super-spine, 2 from leaves (expected).\n  - RIB: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.9; 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.11; expected.\n- Leaf 65200 (leaf_router_0_0)\n  - Neighbors: spines 65100 and 65101 — both Established.\n  - RIB: Connected 10.0.0.0/24; BGP 10.0.1.0/24 via spine 65100 (172.16.0.4). Expected.\n- Leaf 65201 (leaf_router_0_1)\n  - Neighbors: spines 65100 and 65101 — both Established.\n  - RIB: Connected 10.0.1.0/24; BGP 10.0.0.0/24 via spine 65101 (172.16.0.6). Expected.\n\nForwarding and Pathing Observations\n- Intra-pod east–west traffic follows leaf → spine → leaf paths (no super-spine needed), consistent with EBGP and physical adjacencies.\n- Super-spine installs a single best path per prefix pointing to spine 65100; this is expected without BGP multipath enabled.\n\nFindings and Anomalies\n1) Host reachability: Normal\n   - No loss, low RTTs in both directions.\n\n2) BGP adjacency and RIB consistency: Normal\n   - All sessions Established; expected prefixes present on all nodes.\n   - Leaves advertise their /24s; spines learn directly from leaves; super-spine learns from both spines.\n\n3) Benign control-plane asymmetry on spine 65100\n   - Symptom: spine_router_0_0 shows PfxRcd=0 from super-spine; spine_router_0_1 shows PfxRcd=2 from super-spine.\n   - Root cause: Super-spine’s best paths for both /24s currently point to spine 65100 (172.16.0.1). In standard BGP behavior, a router advertises only its selected best path to peers and will not advertise a path back to the neighbor from which that best path was learned (AS-path loop prevention/split-horizon). Hence, spine 65100 receives 0 new routes from the super-spine, while spine 65101 receives 2. This is expected behavior and not a fault.\n\n4) Design observation (not a fault): No ECMP on super-spine\n   - Super-spine selects a single best path for each /24 (both via spine 65100). In Clos designs, ECMP is commonly enabled for path diversity, but its absence here is not causing any current issue.\n\nConclusion\n- Overall network health is good. Data and control planes are consistent with the intended EBGP Clos design. No service-impacting anomalies detected. The observed asymmetric prefix reception at spine 65100 is an expected outcome of BGP best-path selection and advertisement rules, not a malfunction.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6000, "output_tokens": 5365, "total_tokens": 11365, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5760}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4160}}}
